snippet.title: Wrath of Salaar | Music By Ravi Basrur | Hombale Films
snippet.description:
Witness the vengeance, feel the power - Wrath of Salaar 

From the Makers of  "KGF: Chapter 1 & 2," &  the visionary director Prashanth Neel, comes a film that will push the boundaries of cinematic brilliance, presenting you the First Single of "Salaar", featuring the powerhouse talents of Prabhas, Prithviraj, Shruthi Haasan, Tinu Anand, Eshwari Rao, Jagapathi Babu, Sriya Reddy, Garuda Ram.  
Brace yourself for an extraordinary tale of rebellion filled with power-packed action and impactful music by Ravi Basrur. 
Rebel Star Prabhas shines as Salaar, Directed by Prasanth Neel, and produced by Hombale Films.
 
Get Ready to Rebel with us and witness the most violent man on screens this Dec 22, 2023.

snippet.title: RBI Bans PayTM in INDIA | PayTM FASTag, Wallet, UPI Going To Close After 29th Feb 2024 | SidTalk
snippet.description:
Hey Guys,
In this video you'll get to know that RBI bans PayTM Payments Bank & Its services like: PayTM UPI, PayTM Wallet, PayTM FASTag, NCMC Card, Prepaid Cards, etc.
Other paytm service: PayTM QR, POS Machine, Soundbox, Payment Gateway will work?
Action against Paytm Payments Bank Ltd under Section 35A of the Banking Regulation Act, 1949
Explained: Why RBI Has Put Restrictions On Paytm Payments Bank
Common question by PayTM customers:
My NCMC Card will stop working?,
My POS Machine/Soundbox not work?,
My Fast Tag will stop working?

PayTM said services will work as Paytm to expand its existing relationships with leading third-party banks to distribute payments and financial services products.

0:00 Intro

0:48 PayTM Business Timeline
1:40 PayTM One97 Communication Services
3:29 RBI Ban Rules Point Wise

snippet.title: Janaabe Jaaniya (Official Video) Gulraj Singh, Javed Ali | Ayaan Zubair, Riva Arora | Manoj Yadav
snippet.description:
VYRL Originals invites you to experience the first flush of childhood love with our latest "Janaabe Jaaniya". Sung by the popular singer Javed Ali, composed by Gulraj Singh & written by Manoj Yadav. Janaabe Jaaniya is sweet harkening ode to the excitement of the puppy love - two young hearts who cross paths to mark the start of an innocent  and beautiful relationship. The video features fresh popular faces - Riva Arora known for her work in Bollywood films & Ayyan Zubair - who is raking up the image of being a digital heartthrob. Watch the video where love and personal Achievement merge , through a song that is an ode to fresh puppy love.

snippet.description:
Hello Friends ! Jo jaisa dikhta hai kabhi kabhi hota nahin hai. Have you ever imagined life without parents, main to sapne mein bhi aisa soch nahi sakti. Chalo dekhein kya hai woh jo mere yaani ki Shanaya ke sath hua ki saari duniya ulat plat hogayi.

Leher

About MaaTri Media 

MaaTri, represents the most beautiful relationship between a mother and a daughter - Nisha Topwal & Anantya Anand aka. MyMissAnand. MaaTri is formed through a combination of two Hindi words - Maa (Mother) and PuTri (daughter) that brings forth energy, enthusiasm and determination to spread positive vibes through their outstanding content. Their content revolves around fashion, food, comedy, parenting, travel, glimpse of their family and simple day-to-day activities that both enjoy doing together. 
The duo captures a contemporary lifestyle of entrepreneur and food blogger mom and a teenage daughter and a social media influencer and shows how they both manage their work, school and personal life - simple pleasure of growing together, through engaging videos and fun visuals. Every post is curated and designed to make the audience laugh, learn, smile and entertain. 

#MyMissAnand #anantyaanand #momdad #lifewithoutyou #maabaap #relatives #maatrimedia #parents

The age of late 20s early 30s come with a longing for a partner, let this rom-com (romantic comedy) make you giggle and smile. find out how Kriti (Played by Plabita Borthakur, known for her role in PK, Lipstick Under My Burkha, and Breathe: Into the Shadows) finds the one, the love of her life. would it be her best friend Jai (Played by Aaron Arjun Koul known for his role in The Price of Free, Baked and Independent Lens, and Mehr in @girliyapa's Who's Your Gynac ) ? Or a walking talking green flag Raghav (Played by Vishal Vashishtha, known for his role in Amazon MiniTV's Hustlers) she met from Jeevansaathi and went on a couple of dates with. Would Jai make it out of this "friend-zone"? Would Raghav get some clarity¬†and¬†answers?

About the show: 
----------------------------------------------------------------------
Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah is a SAB Comedy Show inspired by the famous humorous column, Duniya Ne Undha Chashmah written by the eminent Gujarati writer, Mr. Tarak Mehta. This show revolves around the Gada family which consists of businessman, Jethalal Champaklal Gada, Jethalal's wife, Daya & their naughty son, Tipendra Gada living in Gokuldham Co-operative Society, and covers topical issues that are socially relevant. This hilarious show will surely tickle your funny bone.

Presenting the interim Union Budget in Parliament this morning, Union Finance Minister Nirmala Sitharaman announced that there would be no change in tax rates for direct and indirect taxes, including import duties. Meanwhile, the fiscal deficit for 2024-25 is estimated at 5.1 per cent of GDP against 5.8 per cent in the current financial year.

Presenting the interim Union Budget in Parliament this morning, Union Finance Minister Nirmala Sitharaman announced that there would be no change in tax rates for direct and indirect taxes, including import duties. Meanwhile, the fiscal deficit for 2024-25 is estimated at 5.1 per cent of GDP against 5.8 per cent in the current financial year.

Khaie Episode 12 [Eng Sub] Digitally Presented by Sparx Smartphones - Faysal Quraishi - Durefishan Saleem - 1st February 2024 - Har Pal Geo

Khaie Digitally Presented by Sparx Smartphones #shinewithsparx
Get Ready to be Enthralled by 'Khaie' - Brought to You by Geo TV with the Cutting-Edge Innovation of Sparx Smartphone as the Exclusive Digital Presenting Partner. A Spectacular Journey Awaits

The story is a revenge saga that unfolds against the backdrop of the ancient tradition of Khaie, where the male members of an enemy's family are eliminated to stop the continuation of their lineage.  At the center of this age-old vendetta are Darwesh Khan, Duraab Khan, and his son Channar Khan, with Zamdaa, the daughter of Darwesh, bearing the heaviest consequences.  
Darwesh Khan is haunted by his father's murder at the hands of Duraab Khan. Seeking a peaceful life, Darwesh aims to broker a truce to end generational enmity. However, suspicions arise, and Duraab Khan and his son Channar Khan doubt Darwesh's intentions for peace.
Despite the genuine efforts of Darwesh, a kind-hearted man with a message for peace, a tragic turn of events unfolds during a celebration at Darwesh's home, causing immense suffering for Zamdaa and her family.
Will Zamdaa bow down in front of her enemies? If not, then will Zamdaa be able to take revenge on her family culprits? Will Zamdaa find allies in her journey, or will she face her enemies alone?

Written By: Saqlain Abbas
Directed By: Syed Wajahat Hussain
Produced By: Abdullah Kadwani & Asad Qureshi
Production House: 7th Sky Entertainment

Cast:
Faysal Quraishi as Channar Khan

The story is a revenge saga that unfolds against the backdrop of the ancient tradition of Khaie, where the male members of an enemy's family are eliminated to stop the continuation of their lineage.  At the center of this age-old vendetta are Darwesh Khan, Duraab Khan, and his son Channar Khan, with Zamdaa, the daughter of Darwesh, bearing the heaviest consequences.  
Darwesh Khan is haunted by his father's murder at the hands of Duraab Khan. Seeking a peaceful life, Darwesh aims to broker a truce to end generational enmity. However, suspicions arise, and Duraab Khan and his son Channar Khan doubt Darwesh's intentions for peace.
Despite the genuine efforts of Darwesh, a kind-hearted man with a message for peace, a tragic turn of events unfolds during a celebration at Darwesh's home, causing immense suffering for Zamdaa and her family.
Will Zamdaa bow down in front of her enemies? If not, then will Zamdaa be able to take revenge on her family culprits? Will Zamdaa find allies in her journey, or will she face her enemies alone?
